            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR1e0001-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_006-98a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-27T02:25:16.844+09:00">Since that man has united a grand and brash nature with hardness,79 On this interpretation, see Yang, 2:541.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_006-98a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:09:17.679+09:00">how could he die a natural death?</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_009-484a.58" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:14:06.521+09:00">Perhaps this refers to how results must come from one’s own integrity.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_009-484a.59" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:14:16.771+09:00">When good faith comes from one’s own integrity,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_009-485a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:14:38.166+09:00">then achievements canbe recorded.”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.76" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:41:02.932+09:00">By command of kings and covenant elders</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.77" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:41:11.423+09:00">theborders were drawn out;</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.78" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:41:18.072+09:00">officers were set up for these borders,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.79" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:41:28.313+09:00">andthey were marked with signs and flags</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.80" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:41:36.336+09:00"> and noted in statutes andregulations,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.81" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:41:42.409+09:00">so that transgressors would be punished.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_010-19a.82" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-01-12T22:43:59.183+09:00">But still theborders could not be maintained.42</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_012-265a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-06-24T21:42:45.218+09:00">Now you propose to attack them,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_012-265a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-06-24T21:42:46.725+09:00">but how can it bedone?”</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_012-265a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-06-24T21:46:15.246+09:00">Our lord said,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR1e0001_tls_012-265a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2024-06-24T21:47:19.182+09:00">“Lu has been weaker thanQi for a long time.</seg>
                </p>
